spanGrp.span: Beteũ jiska jui kã' wa/kabata nã
people lived in Talamanca and Ujarraz.
They… went… to fetch thing there on the other side, things like pigs… uh… cows, things like… they would bring things which they would exchange for bananas, manioc and other things;
Jie-wa të mi-gẽ jirö jirö tsõ jamĩwa jamĩga ta jirö jirö kuchi bi esteee baga mĩna bi jebi esteee jie-wa të jirö tse-gẽ je je interkambiawẽ-gẽ chomõ ra shkö bi
they would exchange them like that.
jirö bi je je je interkambiawẽ-gẽ jebi nã
My grandfather used to tell things, but he used to tell… uh he would tell them [but] I forgot how he would tell them.
Tatiga tatiga yís tatiga të jirö page-gẽ pero page-gẽ esteee í page-gẽ í jẽr yís jẽr shena'-wã menẽbi í të í page-gẽ
